    <!-- <CustomVideo client:load /> -->
    <BodyContainer idName="tcnj-spirit" client:load>
      <h2>
        The spirit of The College of New Jersey embodies collaboration,
        creativity, accessibility, and inclusion.
      </h2>
      <p>
        The building structure will integrate flexibility, sustainability, and
        efficient space utilization with acoustics and performance technologies.
        Integral to the flexible functionality of the building is a retractable
        door that opens to a covered, multi-purpose outdoor seating area. The
        Pavilion will function year-round in a central location on campus. This
        innovative public space will provide an ideal location for next-level
        partnerships: Think science and business researchers joined by scholars,
        dancers, artists, and linguists to explore their interdisciplinary and
        creative potential.
      </p>
    </BodyContainer>

    <CarouselContainer
      carouselImages={[
        { image: "/astro/images/pav-1.jpg", alt: "Pavilion Rendering 1" },
        { image: "/astro/images/pav-2.jpg", alt: "Pavilion Rendering 2" },
        { image: "/astro/images/pav-3.jpg", alt: "Pavilion Rendering 3" },
      ]}
      client:load
    >
      <div id="carousel-body">
        <p>
          The space will feature a retractable, garage-like door and materials
          that blend with the environment while maintaining the signature look
          and feel of TCNJ’s campus.
        </p>
        <a class="button-link"> Download TCNJ Pavilion Campaign Overview</a>
      </div>
    </CarouselContainer>
    <GiveBanner client:load>
      <h2>Giving Opportunities</h2>
      <p>
        Please join the TCNJ community in support of this important new project.
        Whether through an individual gift or sponsorship, there are numerous
        ways to be involved with the creation of the TCNJ Pavilion.
      </p>

      <p>
        Naming opportunities will underwrite various aspects of programming
        provided through the TCNJ Pavilion, including but not limited to support
        for the naming of the space/facility; recurring programs and
        initiatives; student organizations’ use of the space; lecture series and
        scholarly panels; and visiting artists and scholar-in-residence
        fellowships.
      </p>
      <a class="button-link">Give Online</a>
    </GiveBanner>
    <Footer>
      <p id="contact-info" class="wrapper">
        General contact info with email@tcnj.edu and 609-771-5555 / 800.347.5555
      </p>
      <hr />
      <img src="" alt="TCNJ" />
    </Footer>
    <!-- <VideoComponent client:load /> -->
  </main>
</Layout>
